text: 199 Byblis (minor planet designation: 199 Byblis) is a medium-sized main belt asteroid. It was discovered by C. H. F. Peters on July 9, 1879, in Clinton, New York and named after Byblis, an incestuous lover in Greek mythology. ==References== ==External links== * * Category:Background asteroids Byblis Byblis Byblis Category:X-type asteroids (SMASS) 18790709
